NN ` , then ` F ( n ) = sum_ k || n ` ` mmu ( k ) G ( n / k ) = sum_ k || n mmu ( n / k ) G ( k ) ` , i.e. the Möbius function is the Dirichlet convolution inverse of the constant function ` 1 ` . Theorem 2.9 in [ApostolNT] p. 32. (Contributed by Mario Carneiro, 2-Jul-2015.)
